The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 China clinch both singles titles

New Delhi: China made a clean sweep, clinching both the mens and womens singles titles after rendering the finals an all-China affair in the 18th Asian Cup table tennis championship here on Tuesday. 

The semi-finals earlier in the day saw the Chinese make it to the title rounds in both the sections to ensure all the top honours were bagged by their paddlers.Olympic silver medallist Wang Hao, ranked fifth, won 17-15, 11-6, 11-9, 13-11 against countryman Shuai Hao to pocket the winners cheque of $5,000. 

Gua Yan comfortably beat Li Xiao Xia 11-4, 11-7, 12-10, 11-8 to emerge champion in the girls section and earned $4,000. 

The mens final threw some exciting contest as both Wang and Shuai displayed some fast attacking game to outplay each other. 

Though Shuai put up a fight in every game, when it came to giving the finishing touches, it was Wang who kept his nerves and called the shots. 

Shuai made a last ditch effort, saving two match points in the fourth game, but finally gave up 13-11The womens final was a one-sided affair with world No. 3 Yan Guo outplaying the 15th ranked Li Xiao Xi. 

Earlier in the day, both the semi-finals threw up exciting contests. Top seed Wang had to work hard against world No. 23 Li Ching of Hong Kong 8-11, 11-8, 10-12, 11-5, 11-7, 11-5 to book a final berth. 

Hao Shuai also had a tough time beating Yang Zi of Singapore 11-7, 11-6, 6-11, 9-11, 7-11, 11-9. (PTI) 




